 Here's something I posted a few days ago about live output to the browser. This will work within a route or controller but you will hit header issues if you try to do certain things after the output has started.

Here's my custom function from my util system. This wont work under all host setups, but has proven pretty reliable.

Top of your function you need

    ob_implicit_flush(true);

And here's the function you can send your message (output) to each time you want it to echo. Change the uSleep() time to have it wait longer before processing the next message (can be set to 0 if you want)

    function bSend($message)
    {
        echo $message."br/";
        echo str_pad('',4096)."\n";
        ob_flush();
        flush();
        usleep(1500);
    }

